scope: v2-swift-busi-real-app-runtime-gaps (SPRINT.md) — final known blocker
  to running busi's real app.ssc as a native app end-to-end. busi's own
  tt(key, base): Any = computedSignal(...) intentionally passes a live
  NativeUiSignal into fieldColumn's title parameter (reactive i18n column
  titles; real, working behavior on busi's production JS frontend).
  SwiftNativeUiHost.scala's column() native binding only accepts a plain
  String, so this fails at runtime with "textColumn title must be String".
next: research how the existing SignalHeadingNode/SignalTextNode/
  SignalButtonNode reactive-variant pattern is built (descriptor + renderer)
  in SwiftNativeUiHost.scala/SwiftNativeUiApple.scala, then extend
  NativeUiColumn's title (and check other column() string args + action
  labels using the same tt() helper) to accept either a plain String or a
  NativeUiSignal, propagating reactivity through to the SwiftUI renderer.
  Verify against busi's real app.ssc (fast raw-swiftc harness) + full
  v2SwiftBackend/test before landing.
